  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-19",
    "date": "2021-08-18T19:59:56Z",
    "text": "Stop shielding Assets from Corporate Known Liability by Eliminating non-debtor Releases Act or the SACKLER Act \n\nThis bill prohibits a bankruptcy court from releasing claims against non-debtors brought by states, tribes, municipalities, or the federal government. However, the bankruptcy court may issue a stay not exceeding 90 days regarding such a claim.\n\nComplex bankruptcies may involve creditor claims against non-debtors associated with the debtor, such as the debtor's officers, directors, or employees. Currently, in carrying out a bankruptcy plan, certain courts may release non-debtors from liability (there is a circuit split regarding this practice)."
  },
